docs.abstract: Its abrupt closure is raising doubts about the crowded field of streaming services.
docs.snippet: Its abrupt closure is raising doubts about the crowded field of streaming services.
docs.lead_paragraph: Yesterday, Warner Bros. Discovery announced it was shutting down CNN+, the extensively hyped but extremely short-lived streaming service. It will close on April 30, for a total run of less than five weeks. “Well, that was fast,” said Scott Galloway, a professor who was planning to host a CNN+ show on business. Quibi, the ill-fated video platform that was streaming’s previous cautionary tale, lasted seven months.

byline.original: By Andrew Ross Sorkin, Jason Karaian, Vivian Giang, Stephen Gandel, Lauren Hirsch, Jenny Gross and Anna Schaverien

docs.abstract: China’s Covid lockdowns and restrictions are holding up truck drivers who carry crucial components among factories and take products to ports, posing a new disruption to the global supply chain.
docs.snippet: China’s Covid lockdowns and restrictions are holding up truck drivers who carry crucial components among factories and take products to ports, posing a new disruption to the global supply chain.
docs.lead_paragraph: BEIJING — China’s mounting Covid-19 restrictions are creating further disruptions to global supply chains for consumer electronics, car parts and other goods.

headline.main: Lockdowns in China Block Truck Shipments and Close Factories
headline.print_headline: Chinese Covid Lockdowns Hampering Supply Chains

docs.abstract: Apple and Google are pushing privacy changes, but a shift in digital tracking is giving some platforms a bigger advertising advantage.
docs.snippet: Apple and Google are pushing privacy changes, but a shift in digital tracking is giving some platforms a bigger advertising advantage.
docs.lead_paragraph: The internet industry shuddered last year when Apple introduced privacy measures for the iPhone that threatened to upend online tracking and cripple digital advertising. Google pledged similar privacy actions.

headline.main: You’re Still Being Tracked on the Internet, Just in a Different Way

byline.original: By Brian X. Chen and Daisuke Wakabayashi

docs.abstract: How much should the middleman get?
docs.snippet: How much should the middleman get?
docs.lead_paragraph: This week, thousands of people who sell goods on Etsy are going on strike to protest the company’s climbing fees. And what seems to be a fight over a small corner of the internet is really one of the most enduring battles over our digital world.

headline.main: Etsy and the Sameness of Internet Fights
headline.print_headline: Etsy Sellers Take Up a Familiar Internet Fight

docs.abstract: Federal privacy bills, security legislation and antitrust laws to address the power of the tech giants have all failed to advance in Congress, despite hand wringing and shows of bipartisan support.
docs.snippet: Federal privacy bills, security legislation and antitrust laws to address the power of the tech giants have all failed to advance in Congress, despite hand wringing and shows of bipartisan support.
docs.lead_paragraph: In just the last few years, Europe has seen a sweeping law for online privacy take effect, approved far-reaching regulations to curb the dominance of the tech giants and on Saturday reached a deal on new legislation to protect its citizens from harmful online content.

headline.main: As Europe Approves New Tech Laws, the U.S. Falls Further Behind
headline.print_headline: U.S. Lags As Europe Promotes Tech Laws

docs.abstract: Big technology companies are set to report earnings starting Tuesday. The S&P 500 has dropped nearly 8 percent this month, its worst monthly showing since March 2020.
docs.snippet: Big technology companies are set to report earnings starting Tuesday. The S&P 500 has dropped nearly 8 percent this month, its worst monthly showing since March 2020.
docs.lead_paragraph: Stocks slid on Tuesday, adding to a losing streak that has April shaping up to be Wall Street’s worst month in two years.

headline.main: Stocks drop 2.8%, led lower by tech, as April’s slump continues.
headline.print_headline: Stocks Face Worst Month In Two Years

docs.abstract: While the company did better in its first three months of the year than many of its tech peers, it warned that Covid problems in China will be an issue.
docs.snippet: While the company did better in its first three months of the year than many of its tech peers, it warned that Covid problems in China will be an issue.
docs.lead_paragraph: After a year of blistering sales growth, Apple showed that it has a more resilient business than many of its tech peers, even though it cooled off in the first three months of the year.

headline.main: Apple’s growth slows, but still beats Wall Street’s expectations.

docs.abstract: The petition for a union vote continues a trend of organizing at service-sector employers like Starbucks and Amazon.
docs.snippet: The petition for a union vote continues a trend of organizing at service-sector employers like Starbucks and Amazon.
docs.lead_paragraph: Employees at an Apple store in Atlanta filed a petition on Wednesday to hold a union election. If successful, the workers could form the first union at an Apple retail store in the United States.

headline.main: Apple Store workers in Atlanta are the first to formally seek a union.
headline.print_headline: Workers Seek Union Election At Apple Store

byline.original: By Noam Scheiber and Kellen Browning

docs.abstract: Tech companies really want their employees to be happy — or at least less annoyed — about returning. So they’re providing concerts, food trucks and other perks.
docs.snippet: Tech companies really want their employees to be happy — or at least less annoyed — about returning. So they’re providing concerts, food trucks and other perks.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Google employees returned to their mostly empty offices this month, they were told to relax. Office time should be “not only productive but also fun.” Explore the place a little. Don’t book back-to-back meetings.

headline.main: Welcome Back to the Office. Isn’t This Fun?
headline.print_headline: Have Fun Like It’s Your Job
